# Curated GitHub export policy
#
# This repository contains many local working files and large scientific
# datasets. Ignore everything by default, then explicitly track the curated
# GitHub-ready export tree.

*

!.gitignore
!README.md
!github_export/
!github_export/**

# Never track caches or local runtime clutter.
**/__pycache__/
**/*.py[cod]
**/.ipynb_checkpoints/
**/.DS_Store
**/._*
**/.spyder-py3/

# Never track heavy/raw/binary scientific products in normal Git.
**/*.fits
**/*.fit
**/*.fz
**/*.h5
**/*.hdf5
**/*.nc
**/*.npy
**/*.npz
**/*.pkl
**/*.pickle
**/*.tar
**/*.tar.gz
**/*.zip
**/*.7z
**/*.dmg

# Keep generated documents and media out of normal Git unless force-added
# intentionally. Prefer Markdown summaries and CSV manifests.
**/*.docx
**/*.doc
**/*.rtf
**/*.pdf
**/*.png
**/*.jpg
**/*.jpeg
**/*.tif
**/*.tiff
**/*.log

# Keep local run folders out unless curated summaries are copied to
# github_export/results/.
plamb_runs/
hht_env*/
cov_sweeps/
jwst_out/

